Copper producing junior Tiger Resources, whose shares remain voluntarily suspended from the ASX, has spent the last two years implementing a turnaround strategy to bring its 95%-owned Kipoi copper/cobalt operation back to profitability. Having stabilised the mine and process plant, the company will spend 2019 putting in place measures to further enhance operating performance while tapping into new opportunities, executive chairman DAVID FRANCES tells LAURA CORNISH. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 4, 2019 and will be published in full on 22 May 2019 You can read the
